Bipolar disorder, once known as manic-depression, is a psychiatric diagnosis referring to a mental health condition defined by periods of extreme, often inappropriate, and sometimes unpredictable mood states.

Bipolar individuals generally experience mania, hypomania or mixed states alternating with clinical depression and euthymic or normal range of mood over varied periods of time. There are many variations of this disorder. Generally, however, a person with bipolar disorder tends to experience more extreme states of mood than other people, moods which can change quickly (many times a day) or last for months. Mood patterns of this nature are associated with distress and disruption, and a relatively high risk of suicide. Bipolar disorder is also associated with a variety of cognitive deficits, in particular, difficulty in organizing and planning. The disorder may also skew the ability to judge others' emotion, and alter sense of awareness. Bipolar individuals can be overly observant and analytical of their environment, and in some cases paranoid of others.

Bipolar disorder is usually treated with medications that help to stabilize mood, and/or therapy and counselling.

Some studies have suggested that while bipolar disorder alters emotion, there may be a correlation between creativity and bipolar disorder, although it is unclear what the relationship is between the two.

Just because I couldn't scream it from the Roof Tops....I wanted to say to the people I love without question (I didn't put this in any or at all):   
Dear Jermaine,  
You're the best you made my freshmen and sophomore years worth all the drama and head aches. You made long drives back to Philly fun, you made Dorney crazy, and some days you just made me laugh. I don't want to stay here at Albright after you graduate this summer, it'll never be the same...and frankly that's just not good enough.  I love you. 

Dear Sarah (Du), 
It was very hard to come to college with out my high school best friend, I was terrified. But for some reason, seeing your LJ and hearing George say you're doing fine makes me feel so much better. Your comments on my LJ, your cute little pics, sad away messages, your uncanny ability to somehow always feel the same way I do. And probably most of all your kind words when I need them the most, and also your great taste in music. I look up to you Sarah I honestly Du (little play on words there). You're a great person, and a great gift to the future just wait to happen. You're definately a gift to me. I love you. 

Dear Sara (My Roomie), 
You drive me right up a wall, sometimes I just want to sock you right in the nose. And some days I want to be some place else when you come around, and I realize that that's because we're getting to be so close and I don't want to let anybody get too close. But I think I slipped up with you, because at this point you're becoming my best friend, 'my sister, my shrink, my savior'. Keep bugging me, keep making me laugh when I want to cry, and keep buying me coffee ice cream, keep taking me to the diner and telling me crazy stories about squirrels, keep healing me of my fuchsia blindness, playing me Placebo songs, keep asking me how you know I'm know I'm gay, keep making me do impressions of that Indian, keep calling me a filthy pirate whore, but whatever you do....don't give up on me, you know why I say that? Because I love you. 

Dear Ron, 
Shut up. You know I love you fool.

Dear Elizabeth, 
As of this moment at 3:54 a.m., when the sun hasn't risen, when you have a body like a twenty seven year old, while you're the wisest women I know, when you're the only person that just 'gets' it, when there is someone shaving every hair on their body in the bathroom next door, when Brian is probably writing me a new death note, after everyone and Sara's mom came up a told me that our line was the best in the show, while you still have my aviators that look better on you then me, while I owe you seven bucks for the whip, while I owe you my life and my first born child for giving me a good friend, While you understand that friendly obligation, while you're probably denying every nice thing I ever said about you, after I lost everything...everywhere...everytime, before you figure out that you're waisting your time buggering around with me, I just want to say...I love you. I love you like nobodies god dammeram business I do.  

Dear Roadies of  Birth, Life, Company, God's gift to me, 
When every one else leaves me behind, when all the lights are out, when the tavern closes (that I was never even in), when car drives off and I'm chasing behind it blinded by dust, I'll know that no matter what...you'll be there....say you will, like you never said it before. I know this to be true cause when I had no one else, I had you guys. You taught me everything about being myself, you even taught me how to fall correctly off my skateboard. When I'm with you guys I am at my best. I know this. And I knw that this summer in Vegas I'll be inside 'the bubble like whoa.' If I could split my heart into 16 different pieces, you would each have a piece.  I love you. I love you. I love you.  

Dear Nichole (Shug), Trae(Sean Paul) Trae, and Mia (Kiesh), 
My side hurts, I never found my cell phone, that woman in the back of the church with has a ham stuck in her throat,  Billy Blanks won't allow me back in Friendly's and there is a man trying to kill me with a leather gun and you know what...I just don't give a fuck. No matter what my problems are you guys make me forget them. I wish though that my phone time with Nichole Giddens would return ::cough, cough:::... Seriously though crew, you keep me sane, and laughing. Summer is almost here..do I hear doom on South or what? I love you. 

Dear Pete,  
You grew me up. I'll never be the same and neither will you. I love you. 

I'm better for it.

So yeah I don't really want to get on here and just shit talk my friend Jaz, but gosh we've really been tossing for tears these past couple of weeks. It's like neither of us is really getting what the other one is trying to say you know? And gosh, it's bringing me to my very end, I mean it's not even just her, geez it's not even close to just her. I wish so many things were right. Has that ever happened to you? And I'm starting to feel like all I'm doing is giving apologies to everyone, especially her. I know what I am shit, but when you've said you were sorry for things over six times in a three to five day span it really can solidify your negative feelings about yourself. 
It's coming to me that I don't deserve the friends and lovers I've had. The things I've done and haven't done, it's all weighing so heavily on my mind and heart lately. And amongst all this I've lost something of the greatest value to me. I want to strive, I want so badly to make it right and work toward a better newer...everything.  
But all is not lost, I go home tomorrow and I want to come back all brand new or at least not feeling the way I have been lately. I'm supposed to hang out with Ronald, and Mia and my parents and more than anything I want to see my sister Sana.
Alda if you still read this I wanted to say you really made me feel good when you immed me that memory of Sabriyah. I mean Lord knows I've had nothing but bad luck on that damn aim thing, and you and I both know why.

I wanted topost about this earlier....

Okay so recently there have been these cartoons printed in magazines and online about Prophet Muhammad. It's caused outrage amongst Muslims in both Muslim countries and here in America, more so in predominantly Muslim countries. People have been rioting, and boycotting Danish products. People have died. And for those of you who don't know this already I am Muslim. I saw those cartoons and I cried, not just because of what they said but because of what they have done. Let me explain:
Muslim Beliefs on Prophet Muhammad's Image: We do not know what he looks like and so there for we have never drawn pictures or done anything in the way of portraying him. I have been taught that since I was a child. It's a kind of respect so as to say that we could not ourselves create an image as beautiful as what God created. Moreover we do not worship him, we try, in our own lives, to admire him and be like him. That is our way of depicting an image of Prophet Muhammad and his teachings. And so if we ourselves, as Muslims and the only representation of Islam on earth, do not draw him then why would we be comfortable with anyone else doing it?
Islam and Hate: I have been a Muslim for 20 years three months, and nine days; never in my life have I been taught to believe in anything besides peace in Islam. The meaning of the greeting that we are often heard giving to one another is: Peace be upon you. We do not condone hate or violence. Those pictures of my Prophet depicted him as a violent womanizer.
My Thoughts and Feelings: If you know me then you've heard me say at least once that I am a bit of a strange Muslim, but that does not mean I don't love and respect my faith. It is everything I am. I love Islam and Prophet Muhammad more than I can say. And so in light of what has happened as far as the deaths and the offensive cartoons of a man I live my life to be an image of I will be seen with the word "RESPECT" written on my hands everyday until I feel that I am no longer disrespected by not only those cartoonists but those who say things like: "It's about free speech." Not only that but I will also be seen wearing a scarf (my head covering) that says "Respect" on it. Because freedom of speech should not be used as a weapon for disrespecting others.
I SHED TEARS FOR THE LACK OF RESPECT, AS WELL AS THOSE WHO DIED.

Yeah so my holiday at home was well needed. I had a panic attack on Thursday night (Calm down I'm prone to them because of stress disorder). I saw my doctor on Friday afternoon and he decided that I needed to have my dosage of Paxil upped. I feel like a crazy person, I mean that's what they do for crazy people just before they put them in a crazy home, they up their dosage of medication....right?! :::Sigh::: But I'm not sad about it because I've been feeling a lot less skiddish, afraid and believe it or not I SLEPT people I went to sleep. It was nice. Dreams were had!
     Onto the better side of my weekend. Besides playing lazer tag, going goat cart racing, and just having a freaking blast with my family on at the EID, I felt great. At two o'clock in the morning on Saturday (that's going into Sunday) Pete knocked on my door and then called my phone. When I got up I was like ready to kill this man...I was having a nice dream. He got me the best gift ever for my birthday. *Note: I appreciate every gift I've ever gotten scarves, leaves, anything. I love it all. But there's something to say for a gift someone gets because they remember you and the things you say. Doesn't that makes you feel so warm, like you're so...so...someone. Just, I guess it's harder to explain than I thought it would be. But I can say I love it. Like when Mia gave me the ear covering from the ear thermometer that her doctor used when taking her temperature...I loved that.
Anywho He got me a semi-perfect condition The Jam t-shirt. Now, everyone who's ever heard my stupid face talk should know the I absolutely positively love the Jam like nobody's business I do. When he gave it to me he tried to leave (he doesn't like to be around when people open the gifts he gives them) but I opened it too fast. I looked at it, and he said he remembered me saying I loved them. In the words of one Alda Lizzi:"My heart smiled." I'm going to hang it on the wall. It's really hard to find their memorabilia because they broke up so fast. I've liked them since I was nine years old almost.
I am now on the E-board of Club Mode (the fashion club on campus), I am the secretary.
P.S. Drunk People suck


So umm, yeah I have a problem. I always think people dislike me, even when they don't. Usually I begin to hate people because I am under the sure impression that they very much dislike me. I can't turn it off. It's very bad for me because I turn people away, and I lose potential friends because of this. I am even mean to people sometimes, solely because I believe they don't like me. I back myself into a corner where I have no choice but to hate the person in retaliation to the hate that I have talked myself into believing that the person holds for me. This is bad.

So my friend Amy's a fucking genius. I got this in an e-mail from her recently. She and her long term partner broke last spring and she has had trouble getting over him. So she came up with this and swears by it. I thought I'd try it. "So here's the thing it's simple really, just list down things you miss about them 1 being the smallest in value and the highest number being the greatest. If you can give a goal or a short explanation of the thing you've listed.  Put either their full name or their first name and middle and last initials. Then post it some place that you'll see it every day. When the day day comes that you stop thinking about or missing that one thing scratch it off the list." Here's mine.

                                                                                         Gabriel P. M.

  1. Your giggle: you swear you don't have one but you do.
  2. Your fingers when you don't clip your nails: I liked them clipped but I liked them even better when they weren't.
  3. Probably your cooking: The bad pork substitutes.
  4. The way you always wanted to protect me from things: I don't think you understood how nice that felt.
  5. Your never got my jokes: it used to urk me but I miss it now.
  6. Your favorite movie was "I'm not afraid": This is a fact about you that I'd like to stop thinking about every time I go to the video store.
  7. The way your face looked when you explained things about Sicily: you looked so home sick.
  8. Sleeping next to you: I would like to stop waking up hoping to find your face.
  9. The fact that you let me go to sleep with my socks on and then let me peel them off with my feet once I was ready to fall asleep: You always warmed my feet with your feet when I did that.
  10. They way you would have given up any and everything just to be with me: No one will ever do that again, but I have to start to believe it's possible.
